                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6369/510.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Heimke</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-12-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 26, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Heimke says the commander of the United States cruiser <hi rend="italic"
                        >Albany</hi> telegraphs from Corinto that Zelaya left there on Friday for
                    Salina Cruz on a Mexican warship. Mr. Heimke states that he has telegraphed this
                    information to the embassy at Mexico.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
